1
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:37,871
OUR UNIVERSE

2
00:00:48,507 --> 00:00:49,925
What's going on?

3
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,594
What in the world are you doing?

4
00:00:52,678 --> 00:00:54,721
Well, I just...

5
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:01,478
Was this why you approached us
in the first place? For money?

6
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:04,982
I was going to pay it back
once I got this situation sorted out!

7
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:07,401
How can you do this?
This is your own family!

8
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:08,902
You know what? Exactly.

9
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:11,196
Shouldn't family help each other
in times of need?

10
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,322
Am I wrong?

11
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,243
So, it was you

12
00:01:17,703 --> 00:01:19,204
who called the insurance company?

13
00:01:19,705 --> 00:01:21,331
Yeah, what about it?

14
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:23,792
Am I not allowed?

15
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:25,836
Speaking of which

16
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,921
I deserve a part of that insurance money!

17
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:31,008
I raised Woo-jin with my own money.

18
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:33,051
What about Woo-joo?

19
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:34,886
Our Woo-joo is

20
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:36,638
Woo-jin's child!

21
00:01:36,722 --> 00:01:38,765
He's your grandson! Your own bloodline!

22
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:41,727
Fine.

23
00:01:41,977 --> 00:01:43,979
Why don't we include Woo-joo

24
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:47,482
and split it four ways?

25
00:01:50,902 --> 00:01:51,903
Get out.

26
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:56,450
Get out right now!

27
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:57,743
Let go!

28
00:01:57,868 --> 00:01:59,828
You know what I've been through
to get this?

29
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:00,912
Let go.

30
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,644
Are you okay, Hyun-jin?

31
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:28,982
Are you crazy?

32
00:02:29,066 --> 00:02:31,401
MYEONGIN POLICE STATION

33
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,945
Given his lengthy rap sheet
of similar priors

34
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:36,573
and parole status,
he'll be taken into custody immediately.

35
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:39,493
Did you really have no clue
he just got out

36
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:41,036
after serving time for fraud?

37
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:44,414
No.

38
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,752
Mr. Sun, the report says you targeted them

39
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,962
to steal their insurance money
and valuables.

40
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,048
Mr. Sun

41
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:54,549
is this correct?

42
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:55,884
Come on.

43
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:57,803
Just think about it.

44
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:02,224
Raising a kid costs a fortune!

45
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,267
Shouldn't I be compensated

46
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:06,353
for the money I spent on raising him?

47
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:07,813
Just cut it out!

48
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:12,609
Please.

49
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,655
Please stop it.

50
00:03:23,245 --> 00:03:24,329
Mr. Sun.

51
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:31,128
You're Woo-jin's brother, right?

52
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:33,505
And who are you?

53
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:36,258
I'm Jeon Min-cheol,
the Police Captain at the station.

54
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,885
May I have a word with you?

55
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:46,393
OUR UNIVERSE

56
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:56,945
You have to clean the wound
every two to three days.

57
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:59,406
Keep it dry for the next few days.

58
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,744
Come to see a doctor right away
if the wound starts to swell.

59
00:04:03,869 --> 00:04:05,454
- Yes, sir.
- All done.

60
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:06,830
Give her some IV drip.

61
00:04:07,456 --> 00:04:08,540
Thank you.

62
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:15,547
- Hello.
- Hello!

63
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,134
Mr. Park

64
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:23,138
Tae-hyung is
taking care of something urgent.

65
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,639
Should we cancel the meeting?

66
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:26,808
Huh? Mr. Sun, too?

67
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:29,519
Hyun-jin also asked
for a last-minute day-off.

68
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:31,188
Did something happen between them?

69
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:34,900
Sorry,
I couldn't properly introduce myself

70
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:37,611
because I was still too shocked
at the funeral.

71
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:41,865
I was Woo-jin's colleague

72
00:04:44,493 --> 00:04:45,577
at the station.

73
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:49,080
So, what's this thing
you want to tell me so urgently?

74
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:51,208
I've been thinking

75
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,210
about whether I should tell you this

76
00:04:54,336 --> 00:04:56,421
or keep quiet for a very long time

77
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:58,882
because

78
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:02,385
Woo-jin didn't want you
to find out about this.

79
00:05:03,512 --> 00:05:05,263
That was why I hesitated.

80
00:05:05,889 --> 00:05:07,057
What do you mean?

81
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:11,520
Mr. Sun Gyu-tae.

82
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,648
You heard that he served time
for fraud, right?

83
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,317
Yes.

84
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,569
Woo-jin was the one

85
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:21,696
who put him behind bars.

86
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,036
He was also why Woo-jin became
a police officer.

87
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:31,998
Around seven years ago

88
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:34,000
someone filed a case of fraud

89
00:05:34,084 --> 00:05:36,628
at our police station.

90
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:38,463
CRIMINAL COMPLAINT FILED BY PARK SEONG-HO

91
00:05:38,547 --> 00:05:41,591
THE ACCUSED: SUN GYU-TAE

92
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:51,643
- Let me see the front.
- What?

93
00:05:52,269 --> 00:05:54,646
What? You're still on this case?

94
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:57,148
We've got a mountain of other cases
to get through.

95
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,025
Why are you taking so long with that one?

96
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:00,986
Just write a brief report

97
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,487
and let the higher-ups handle it.

98
00:06:02,571 --> 00:06:05,156
He'll only get a year tops
if we let it go.

99
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,576
I'm sure we'll be able to find
way more victims.

100
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,995
But that's not our job. What can we do?

101
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:11,079
Come on.

102
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:12,581
This is odd.

103
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:15,542
Do you know the victim or something?

104
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:19,004
No, but I know the accused.

105
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:21,047
What?

106
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:24,217
That's my father.

107
00:06:24,885 --> 00:06:27,470
Woo-jin spent all his time
looking for the victims

108
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:29,222
Gyu-tae had scammed.

109
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:31,725
So, I asked him

110
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:35,228
what happened between them

111
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:38,315
that he was so determined
to put him in jail.

112
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:48,283
It's just like how every other story goes.

113
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,119
He was just an average man

114
00:06:51,953 --> 00:06:54,331
but his business failed

115
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,875
and he hasn't stopped obsessing
over money since.

116
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,210
And he spent more time
being drunk than not,

117
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,087
and when he was drunk

118
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,299
he kept resorting to violence.

119
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:05,467
What?

120
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:08,803
You're saying

121
00:07:09,304 --> 00:07:10,764
he even beat you?

122
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:14,434
Getting beaten is only hard
the first time.

123
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,562
I just got numb to it after a while.

124
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,441
Then, I saw him

125
00:07:22,192 --> 00:07:24,903
trying to hurt Tae-hyung, too.

126
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,114
That was when I knew.

127
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:32,369
I knew I couldn't just let him
get away with it.

128
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,913
I knew I had to call the cops.

129
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,791
But Gyu-tae doesn't have
other prior convictions.

130
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:41,836
Well, I had a plan.

131
00:07:43,755 --> 00:07:47,509
I planned to leave Tae-hyung
at an orphanage for a bit to keep him safe

132
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,552
and call the cops after that.

133
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,472
I thought that'd work

134
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:56,351
but I failed every time.

135
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:00,480
You know how things were back in the day.

136
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,149
He could just get away with all of it

137
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:05,235
by saying he was teaching me discipline.

138
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,407
I reported him several times

139
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,951
ran away from him

140
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,121
and got beaten once he found me again.

141
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,459
That had repeated nonstop

142
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,212
and a few years had passed
before I knew it.

143
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:26,464
What about your brother?

144
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:28,258
You were young, too. You also needed him

145
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,010
as someone to rely on.

146
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:31,261
That was

147
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:36,474
the only way I could keep Tae-hyung safe

148
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,977
from my father.

149
00:08:40,103 --> 00:08:41,521
Not letting him stay home.

150
00:08:46,985 --> 00:08:49,946
I thought it'd be all over once I grew up

151
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:55,535
but seeing Gyu-tae ask for money
every once in a while

152
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:57,412
made me think

153
00:08:58,872 --> 00:09:01,833
"I'm glad at least Tae-hyung is free

154
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:05,378
from this devil of a human."

155
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:07,881
"What a relief."

156
00:09:09,132 --> 00:09:10,717
Gosh, you're too kind.

157
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:12,427
Why did you

158
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:17,015
bear everything on your own all your life?

159
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:21,811
Because I'm his big brother.

160
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:25,065
That's

161
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:27,442
what an older brother should do.

162
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:30,111
Because he was your older brother.

163
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:40,371
Here.

164
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:51,800
CRIMINAL COMPLAINT

165
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:54,844
Gyu-tae started beating Woo-jin

166
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:56,429
from eighth grade.

167
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,766
As you can tell from the files

168
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:02,393
the violence continued
for quite a few years.

169
00:10:02,477 --> 00:10:04,354
I HAVE A SIX-YEAR-OLD LITTLE BROTHER.
I'M AFRAID HE'LL BE BEATEN, TOO.

170
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,980
It'd been too long

171
00:10:06,064 --> 00:10:08,525
once he got Gyu-tae in prison

172
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:10,527
which was why

173
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:14,531
he couldn't work up the nerve
to go see you again.

174
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,408
No...

175
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:22,372
This can't be. Why...

176
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:28,837
He was worried Gyu-tae would approach you
after his release, too.

177
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,739
TEMPORARY HELPER

178
00:11:08,585 --> 00:11:10,295
Why isn't he picking up?

179
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,996
SUN WOO-JIN

180
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:16,319
<i>Woo-jin told me you were the only thing</i>

181
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:19,656
<i>keeping Woo-jin going.</i>

182
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:32,335
MOONLIGHT ORPHANAGE

183
00:12:36,798 --> 00:12:39,425
<i>He said</i>
<i>he felt like he could handle anything</i>

184
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:44,430
<i>when he saw how well you were doing.</i>

185
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:46,599
<i>What a dummy.</i>

186
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,235
THE 1ST SHUTTA SNAP PHOTO
GRAND PRIZE RECIPIENT, SUN TAE-HYUNG

187
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:59,612
THE 1ST SHUTTA SNAP PHOTO
GRAND PRIZE RECIPIENT, SUN TAE-HYUNG

188
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:07,120
TITLE: "A RAINY DAY"

189
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:21,718
THE 1ST SHUTTA SNAP PHOTO
GRAND PRIZE RECIPIENT, SUN TAE-HYUNG

190
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:34,814
PHOTOGRAPHER: HA JI-YEONG
ASSISTANT: SUN TAE-HYUNG

191
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,360
PHOTOGRAPHER: HA JI-YEONG
ASSISTANT: SUN TAE-HYUNG

192
00:13:45,116 --> 00:13:47,702
Who told you to do that?

193
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:55,376
Who told you to face it all for me?

194
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:02,425
You think I'd appreciate you for it?

195
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:07,680
You...

196
00:14:12,185 --> 00:14:14,896
shouldn't have just left me like this.

197
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:18,566
How could you leave me like that?

198
00:14:23,071 --> 00:14:24,697
What do I do now?

199
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:28,326
Huh?

200
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:32,914
What am I supposed to do now?

201
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:00,525
Oh, I didn't know you were home.

202
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:05,196
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

203
00:15:06,114 --> 00:15:07,990
Sorry, I was just really busy.

204
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,373
You should put on some ointment.

205
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:21,045
What did the doctor say?

206
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:24,841
He said it wasn't a big scar.
It'll be fine.

207
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:27,718
And you?

208
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:30,346
You okay?

209
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:36,018
It's been a long day for you. Rest up.

210
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,603
I'll step out for a bit.

211
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,063
What?

212
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:41,023
You can go to bed first.
Don't wait for me.

213
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:55,079
EONEU RESTAURANT

214
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:11,262
KIM UI-JUN

215
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,354
Remember

216
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:23,274
the day of the accident?

217
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,693
That was the day

218
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:31,032
Woo-jin received a text
about Dad's discharge.

219
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:35,870
<i>Tae-hyung, it's Woo-jin.</i>

220
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:39,457
<i>There's something I have to tell you.</i>
<i>Call me when you can.</i>

221
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,501
That was why he texted me.

222
00:16:41,584 --> 00:16:42,877
To tell me that.

223
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:47,131
But I had no idea.

224
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,177
You didn't know anything.

225
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,638
That's the problem.

226
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,976
I was a total idiot.

227
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:03,064
I just let everyone around me get hurt.

228
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:10,112
Do you think

229
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:15,618
maybe if I called him back

230
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:22,250
Woo-jin and his wife would still be alive?

231
00:17:26,587 --> 00:17:29,632
Why was I in his way until the very end?

232
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:35,263
Everything feels like my fault.

233
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:42,061
If it weren't for me

234
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,607
Woo-jin wouldn't have lived
such a miserable life.

235
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:53,406
And if it weren't for me

236
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:59,203
he wouldn't have died in a car crash.

237
00:17:59,287 --> 00:18:01,247
You can't say that.

238
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,881
I actually went...

239
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:13,259
to his wedding.

240
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:18,556
First, the groom will put the ring
on the bride.

241
00:18:36,824 --> 00:18:38,701
<i>I wished him a not-so-happy life.</i>

242
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:46,000
I should've just wished him
all the happiness in the world.

243
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:54,216
Only if I knew that was my last time...

244
00:18:57,303 --> 00:18:59,055
I shouldn't have said that.

245
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:10,274
Hoppy.

246
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:12,526
It's time to go to bed, Woo-joo.

247
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:14,487
- No.
- Are you not sleepy?

248
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:15,571
No.

249
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:16,906
It's raining.

250
00:19:17,031 --> 00:19:18,532
- Rain?
- Yeah.

251
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:23,621
Uncle.

252
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:25,748
What?

253
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:28,501
You miss your uncle?

254
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:29,627
Yeah.

255
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,630
He said he'd be home late tonight.

256
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:34,840
You should go to bed first.

257
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:35,966
No.

258
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:38,886
- Uncle Woo-jin's heart is
- Yeah.

259
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,222
in a big, big pain.

260
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:42,848
Yeah.

261
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:48,229
It's raining so much now.

262
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:52,358
I hope he's okay.

263
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:55,111
It's raining so much.

264
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:00,658
Rain.

265
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:03,494
Yes.

266
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:05,955
I checked the outfit

267
00:20:06,497 --> 00:20:09,208
and it doesn't seem suitable
for the theme of the shoot.

268
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,668
Please check it.

269
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,086
Thank you.

270
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:17,466
Hey, Tae-hyung.

271
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,762
You look like a total wreck.

272
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:23,681
What happened to your face?

273
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:25,641
Did you fight someone?

274
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,184
It's nothing.

275
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:30,104
Tae-hyung

276
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:33,190
people like us need to take good care
of our faces.

277
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:36,861
Make sure to put this on before bed
every night.

278
00:20:39,864 --> 00:20:40,948
Thank you.

279
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,911
By the way, isn't it your day off today?

280
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,541
I just wanted to keep myself busy.

281
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:53,210
I sent you the edits from the last shoot

282
00:20:53,294 --> 00:20:54,462
so please check them.

283
00:20:54,545 --> 00:20:55,629
Already?

284
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,173
Oh, right.

285
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,800
About ARCO's brand campaign
for the next season.

286
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:02,428
They want to see the proposal for it
as soon as possible.

287
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:04,138
Yeah, I'm almost done with it.

288
00:21:04,847 --> 00:21:06,015
That too? Already?

289
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:07,767
I'll try to get it done by today.

290
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:12,688
How is he so fast

291
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:14,148
when he just joined the team?

292
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:17,318
He's leaving me with no more excuses
to stay on for longer.

293
00:21:27,036 --> 00:21:29,038
CONGRATULATIONS TO THE THREE INTERNS
LANDING PERMANENT POSITIONS

294
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:30,956
WOO HYUN-JIN, CHO JIN-YOUNG,
SHIN JI-MIN

295
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:35,711
Ms. Woo!

296
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:38,631
Congratulations on landing
a permanent contract!

297
00:21:40,049 --> 00:21:42,051
- Congratulations!
- Congrats!

298
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,178
Looks like we'll see you around
for much longer.

299
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,596
- Looking forward to it.
- Congrats.

300
00:21:45,679 --> 00:21:46,722
Thank you.

301
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:48,974
I promise to work even harder.

302
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:50,810
Thank you for celebrating it with me.

303
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:52,937
Congratulations!

304
00:21:58,025 --> 00:21:59,026
- It's so good!
- Yeah.

305
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:00,486
- So good.
- The cake is amazing.

306
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:03,823
Right? I love the cakes at this bakery!

307
00:22:05,366 --> 00:22:07,368
By the way, Ms. Woo and Mr. Park

308
00:22:08,202 --> 00:22:09,954
were you two very close in college?

309
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:11,413
What?

310
00:22:11,914 --> 00:22:14,041
Mr. Park insisted

311
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:16,585
that we had to get the chocolate cake
from this bakery.

312
00:22:16,669 --> 00:22:19,046
He even lined up to get it.

313
00:22:20,548 --> 00:22:23,759
Guys don't usually pick up
on small details like that, do they?

314
00:22:25,928 --> 00:22:28,597
That's why you're still single.

315
00:22:28,681 --> 00:22:30,683
Caring and thoughtful men have no problem

316
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:32,351
remembering these small things.

317
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:34,395
Men like that are popular

318
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:36,021
and have healthy relationships.

319
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:37,731
Women love me, too!

320
00:22:37,815 --> 00:22:39,817
Mr. Popular with zero game? Yeah, sure.

321
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,365
It's so good.

322
00:22:46,824 --> 00:22:48,242
Do you want one more slice?

323
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:52,788
Watch out. It'll get on your blouse.

324
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:54,665
What happened to your arm?

325
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:56,125
Did you get hurt?

326
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:57,710
Huh? You're right.

327
00:22:58,168 --> 00:22:59,587
It looks really bad.

328
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:00,713
No

329
00:23:00,963 --> 00:23:02,464
it just looks really bad

330
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:04,258
because it's wrapped

331
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:05,426
but it's not a big deal.

332
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:09,263
What? Are you sure you're really fine?

333
00:23:10,306 --> 00:23:12,474
See? What did I tell you?

334
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:15,144
I knew something was fishy about that guy
from the get-go!

335
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:18,063
How's your wound healing?

336
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:21,150
I didn't get hurt that badly,
all thanks to Tae-hyung.

337
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:25,321
You really can't trust anyone, huh?

338
00:23:26,739 --> 00:23:28,490
You must've been so surprised.

339
00:23:28,574 --> 00:23:30,784
I'm sure it was worse for Tae-hyung.

340
00:23:33,913 --> 00:23:35,039
But

341
00:23:35,998 --> 00:23:37,625
I can't stop thinking about it.

342
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:39,418
Hmm? About what?

343
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:40,753
You know

344
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:42,671
I wonder if I brought this onto us

345
00:23:42,755 --> 00:23:45,132
because I kept pushing Tae-hyung
to connect with his dad.

346
00:23:45,215 --> 00:23:47,134
I kept pushing Tae-hyung
to talk to his dad

347
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:48,844
when he didn't want to.

348
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:53,098
I kept saying he couldn't cut
his own father off

349
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:56,477
insisting that he must've had
his reasons, too.

350
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:58,771
Shouldn't you

351
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:01,148
sit him down and talk about this?

352
00:24:02,608 --> 00:24:03,692
Should I?

353
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:05,527
Of course!

354
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:08,113
You and Tae-hyung are still family
at the end of the day.

355
00:24:08,906 --> 00:24:10,324
You should help each other

356
00:24:10,407 --> 00:24:12,868
in times of need, you know?

357
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:17,581
- Hmm?
- Yeah.

358
00:24:21,502 --> 00:24:22,503
Ms. Baek.

359
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:26,840
Yes?

360
00:24:27,299 --> 00:24:28,634
Do you have a minute?

361
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,513
Me?

362
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:35,724
It's nothing big.

363
00:24:36,475 --> 00:24:38,018
I just have a question.

364
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:44,191
Do you know what's up with Hyun-jin's arm?

365
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:46,902
Sorry?

366
00:24:46,986 --> 00:24:50,572
I was worried
when she suddenly took a day off

367
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:53,325
but couldn't ask her
because she said it was a family matter.

368
00:24:54,034 --> 00:24:55,577
Did she get hurt that day?

369
00:24:55,995 --> 00:24:56,996
How?

370
00:24:57,079 --> 00:24:59,790
Oh, that's... Well...

371
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:04,503
It's a personal matter.
You should ask her, not me.

372
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:05,921
I'm just worried.

373
00:25:07,006 --> 00:25:10,092
I know she'll say it's nothing
if I ask her.

374
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:14,138
I don't know
why she looks out for everyone else

375
00:25:14,722 --> 00:25:16,640
but never herself.

376
00:25:21,311 --> 00:25:23,188
I really shouldn't tell you, though.

377
00:25:26,567 --> 00:25:29,653
Oh, there's your auntie.

378
00:25:29,737 --> 00:25:30,738
- Auntie!
- Hyun-jin!

379
00:25:30,821 --> 00:25:31,822
- It's your auntie!
- Hyun-jin!

380
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:33,824
- Hi, Hyun-jin.
- Hi!

381
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:35,576
Woo-joo.

382
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:38,912
This is why

383
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:41,123
you can never judge a book by its cover.

384
00:25:41,915 --> 00:25:44,209
Gosh, I totally fell for it, too.

385
00:25:44,293 --> 00:25:45,627
I know!

386
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:48,130
We were also so surprised to hear that.

387
00:25:48,464 --> 00:25:49,465
I hear

388
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:51,800
it was also Woo-joo's grandfather

389
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:53,469
who broke into your home last time.

390
00:25:53,594 --> 00:25:55,846
I knew something was off.

391
00:25:55,929 --> 00:25:57,681
The burglar who got caught insisted

392
00:25:57,765 --> 00:26:00,267
he never robbed Unit 206.

393
00:26:00,768 --> 00:26:03,937
And I once caught Gyu-tae

394
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:07,149
glancing at the door lock keypad.

395
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,942
Really?

396
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:11,695
My gosh, I was so clueless.

397
00:26:11,779 --> 00:26:14,323
I judged Tae-hyung for being heartless
for no reason.

398
00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:15,491
I feel bad now.

399
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:19,203
It's okay. We didn't know better.

400
00:26:19,286 --> 00:26:22,039
How's Tae-hyung doing?

401
00:26:22,414 --> 00:26:24,500
The last time I saw him

402
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:27,169
he'd lost so much weight.
He was thin as a rail.

403
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,088
Of course.

404
00:26:29,171 --> 00:26:30,672
He almost got scammed

405
00:26:30,756 --> 00:26:32,591
by none other than his own father.

406
00:26:32,674 --> 00:26:34,051
How can this be real?

407
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:36,970
Should I get some <i>makgeolli</i>
so we can talk over some drinks?

408
00:26:37,054 --> 00:26:39,348
No, don't bother him.

409
00:26:40,641 --> 00:26:43,602
It's best to leave him alone
at a time like this.

410
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:46,605
That's family for you.

411
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:48,899
It pains you to have one

412
00:26:50,526 --> 00:26:53,654
but it also pains you not to.

413
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:12,464
You home?

414
00:27:12,923 --> 00:27:14,091
What's all this?

415
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:16,593
I thought I'd grab a beer with you.

416
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:22,558
Where's Woo-joo?

417
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:25,561
He's at Bom's.
He wants to play with Ga-eul more.

418
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:39,241
You seem really busy lately.

419
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:41,160
You haven't had a day off in so long.

420
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:44,371
You know.

421
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,874
It's just been busy lately.

422
00:27:48,292 --> 00:27:49,793
I know you're going through a lot.

423
00:27:51,003 --> 00:27:52,462
You seem so exhausted

424
00:27:52,546 --> 00:27:54,590
ever since the incident with your father.

425
00:27:56,967 --> 00:27:59,052
Let me know anytime if you need my help.

426
00:27:59,845 --> 00:28:01,513
You stayed by my side and helped me

427
00:28:01,597 --> 00:28:03,348
when I was struggling at work.

428
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:06,727
Don't feel like you have to carry it all
by yourself.

429
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:09,521
Come to me if you ever need to talk.

430
00:28:10,272 --> 00:28:12,733
You can lean on me. We're family.

431
00:28:17,196 --> 00:28:18,322
Family...

432
00:28:21,742 --> 00:28:23,285
I don't have such a thing.

433
00:28:24,828 --> 00:28:25,829
Hmm?

434
00:28:26,246 --> 00:28:27,748
You saw it yourself.

435
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:32,753
How my real family treats me.

436
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:36,215
So, what family?

437
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:41,803
You're bumming me out.

438
00:28:42,221 --> 00:28:45,098
I know your father's been giving you
a really hard time

439
00:28:45,182 --> 00:28:46,683
but what about Woo-joo and me?

440
00:28:46,934 --> 00:28:48,477
Aren't we family to you?

441
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,354
Family? What does it even mean?

442
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:54,441
I tried to trust my only family

443
00:28:55,275 --> 00:28:56,777
who abandoned me, and look.

444
00:28:58,070 --> 00:29:00,197
That hurt you, too.

445
00:29:03,951 --> 00:29:05,535
This wouldn't have happened

446
00:29:05,619 --> 00:29:07,579
if I hadn't trusted him from the start.

447
00:29:17,839 --> 00:29:20,801
Thank you for this, and I'm sorry

448
00:29:23,220 --> 00:29:24,638
but I need to head in.

449
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:58,880
PARK YOON-SEONG FROM BS FOOD

450
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:09,308
What's wrong?

451
00:30:13,103 --> 00:30:15,063
What's taking your uncle so long?

452
00:30:15,147 --> 00:30:16,440
Maybe he's busy with work.

453
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:18,191
We barely get to see him now.

454
00:30:21,695 --> 00:30:22,988
Mommy...

455
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:25,615
Uncle...

456
00:30:27,909 --> 00:30:29,494
Mommy...

457
00:30:32,873 --> 00:30:33,999
Here.

458
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:36,001
Open up.

459
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:39,504
Here. Open.

460
00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:44,760
Why? You have to eat more to grow.

461
00:30:45,719 --> 00:30:48,430
You ate your uncle's food just fine.

462
00:30:48,513 --> 00:30:49,598
Why not mine?

463
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:51,016
Here. Open!

464
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:53,393
Come on, try it.

465
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:55,812
If you don't eat it

466
00:30:55,896 --> 00:30:58,565
I'm going to eat it all!

467
00:31:00,484 --> 00:31:01,693
Open up!

468
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,784
Just a bit. Open!

469
00:31:17,793 --> 00:31:20,128
Fine. You don't want to eat?

470
00:31:20,212 --> 00:31:21,213
No.

471
00:31:21,296 --> 00:31:23,090
Okay, let's not eat, then.

472
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:25,092
You don't have to eat.

473
00:31:29,221 --> 00:31:30,472
Darn it.

474
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:31,848
Who's calling?

475
00:31:32,682 --> 00:31:34,017
Hello?

476
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:35,852
<i>Hey, it's me.</i>

477
00:31:36,436 --> 00:31:37,437
Sorry?

478
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:39,147
TEAM LEADER PARK YOON-SEONG

479
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:42,442
Hey, Yoon-seong! What's up?

480
00:31:42,526 --> 00:31:43,985
Nothing much.

481
00:31:44,486 --> 00:31:45,695
What are you doing today?

482
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:48,407
I'm going to spend the day with Woo-joo.

483
00:31:50,075 --> 00:31:52,160
It's just us two at home.

484
00:31:52,285 --> 00:31:53,412
I see.

485
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:57,082
Can I go to your house for a bit?

486
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,126
I have something for Woo-joo.

487
00:31:59,626 --> 00:32:00,710
Right now?

488
00:32:03,588 --> 00:32:04,673
Ta-da.

489
00:32:04,881 --> 00:32:05,924
What's this?

490
00:32:06,007 --> 00:32:08,218
I hear this is super popular
among kids these days.

491
00:32:08,677 --> 00:32:11,054
You don't need to get him things.

492
00:32:11,138 --> 00:32:12,806
It's my gift for your new contract.

493
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,933
Think of it as a bonus
from your supervisor.

494
00:32:16,393 --> 00:32:18,019
Okay, thank you.

495
00:32:21,231 --> 00:32:22,983
I was just feeding Woo-joo.

496
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:27,529
- And you?
- What?

497
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:28,613
Did you eat?

498
00:32:29,281 --> 00:32:30,824
No, not yet.

499
00:32:31,533 --> 00:32:33,118
Why don't we have

500
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:34,453
our second date today, then?

501
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:02,939
I just made some simple things
with what you had.

502
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:05,066
And I seasoned
the fried rice you made more.

503
00:33:05,317 --> 00:33:09,446
You did way more than just seasoning it.

504
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:13,241
How do you clean as you cook?

505
00:33:14,034 --> 00:33:16,786
You're so full of surprises.

506
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:18,955
I didn't think you'd be good with chores.

507
00:33:19,039 --> 00:33:21,124
You don't give me enough credit, do you?

508
00:33:21,374 --> 00:33:24,878
No, I'm just impressed. I mean it.

509
00:33:26,296 --> 00:33:28,882
I've been doing chores since I was a kid.

510
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:32,636
You cooked and did chores
since you were a kid?

511
00:33:32,719 --> 00:33:33,720
You?

512
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:38,141
Woo-joo seems to love what I got for him.

513
00:33:38,266 --> 00:33:39,267
Hmm?

514
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:43,522
Woo-joo!

515
00:33:45,190 --> 00:33:46,483
Here, give it to me.

516
00:33:46,566 --> 00:33:48,485
Good boy!

517
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:51,988
Hi, Woo-joo.

518
00:33:52,072 --> 00:33:53,657
You want to take down the bad guy?

519
00:33:54,574 --> 00:33:55,617
Is it yours?

520
00:33:55,992 --> 00:33:57,202
Bad guy!

521
00:34:07,128 --> 00:34:08,463
Look at this, Woo-joo!

522
00:34:11,424 --> 00:34:12,467
Wow!

523
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:36,616
Do you want to blow bubbles?

524
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:41,705
Yoon-seong, you're pretty good with kids.

525
00:34:42,831 --> 00:34:44,583
I had a lot of younger siblings.

526
00:34:45,125 --> 00:34:47,168
Glad I'm finally putting
my babysitting skills

527
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:49,212
to use today.

528
00:34:49,713 --> 00:34:50,714
Younger siblings?

529
00:34:52,007 --> 00:34:54,926
Why did I think you were an only child?

530
00:34:55,635 --> 00:34:56,720
Because I am.

531
00:34:58,847 --> 00:35:01,182
I was adopted in middle school.

532
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:06,271
It was my job to babysit the kids

533
00:35:06,813 --> 00:35:08,898
when I was at the orphanage.

534
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:13,653
I was so popular among kids, you know?

535
00:35:16,197 --> 00:35:17,240
Did that surprise you?

536
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:20,869
No, I'm not surprised.

537
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:23,079
I just didn't know.

538
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:26,291
It's not a big deal to me anymore.

539
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:29,336
I wasn't purposely trying to hide it

540
00:35:30,837 --> 00:35:33,131
but the subject just never came up
until now.

541
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:39,137
What a lucky guy you are.

542
00:35:41,222 --> 00:35:43,975
You've grown
into such a strong and incredible person.

543
00:35:44,267 --> 00:35:47,145
I bet your parents must've been
really great people.

544
00:35:48,605 --> 00:35:50,023
You can't get luckier than that.

545
00:35:52,275 --> 00:35:53,276
Yeah.

546
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:54,903
Hyun-jin

547
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:58,823
that's why I can tell you this for sure.

548
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:03,703
Thankfully, I met a good family

549
00:36:04,204 --> 00:36:05,830
and was raised with so much love.

550
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:10,543
So, I know how to give love

551
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:12,420
better than anyone.

552
00:36:13,755 --> 00:36:15,173
I don't believe

553
00:36:15,799 --> 00:36:18,134
there's only one way
a family should be, either.

554
00:36:20,595 --> 00:36:23,682
I can be an umbrella

555
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:26,142
you and Woo-joo can always count on.

556
00:36:28,228 --> 00:36:29,854
I promise to stand strong

557
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,524
and shield you two from any storm.

558
00:36:34,109 --> 00:36:35,985
If you'll just let me.

559
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,054
I heard

560
00:37:03,722 --> 00:37:06,808
about what happened to Hyun-jin's arm.

561
00:37:09,269 --> 00:37:11,938
You said so yourself.
That you were her family

562
00:37:12,564 --> 00:37:14,149
so there was nothing to worry about.

563
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:15,400
But look at her now.

564
00:37:17,193 --> 00:37:18,778
What happened to being family?

565
00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:21,948
How could you put your own family
in such danger?

566
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:24,367
You've put Hyun-jin in danger

567
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:26,703
too many times.

568
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:29,539
I don't know anymore.

569
00:37:30,165 --> 00:37:33,501
I can't tell if you're doing your part
as her family

570
00:37:34,002 --> 00:37:36,337
or just bringing more trouble
into Hyun-jin's life.

571
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:53,897
Tae-hyung.

572
00:37:59,152 --> 00:38:01,404
I feel terrible right now.

573
00:38:01,863 --> 00:38:03,531
Send some money to my inmate account.

574
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:05,533
Just so we're clear

575
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:08,203
I'm not settling or going easy on you.

576
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:10,330
You...

577
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,624
This is your father you're talking to!

578
00:38:12,707 --> 00:38:14,292
You shouldn't have...

579
00:38:16,753 --> 00:38:19,088
You shouldn't have done that
if you had a heart.

580
00:38:21,382 --> 00:38:22,550
Woo-jin...

581
00:38:24,177 --> 00:38:26,429
What did that little boy ever do to you

582
00:38:26,513 --> 00:38:28,097
to deserve that kind of beating?

583
00:38:29,766 --> 00:38:31,351
And you call yourself a father?

584
00:38:31,893 --> 00:38:34,103
How dare you?

585
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:38,107
After ruining Woo-jin's life,
and now, mine, too?

586
00:38:38,191 --> 00:38:40,902
I don't know
what you've been told from whom

587
00:38:41,069 --> 00:38:43,571
but I have my side of the story, too!

588
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:45,490
I can't believe the nerve you have.

589
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:47,450
Sure.

590
00:38:48,535 --> 00:38:49,953
That's more like you.

591
00:38:51,663 --> 00:38:53,039
I'll continue to live

592
00:38:54,749 --> 00:38:56,793
and tell myself I have no family.

593
00:38:56,876 --> 00:38:58,461
So, let me warn you.

594
00:39:00,713 --> 00:39:03,550
Don't ever let me see your face again.

595
00:39:04,801 --> 00:39:07,345
- What?
- You and I!

596
00:39:08,972 --> 00:39:10,598
We're over for good.

597
00:39:12,892 --> 00:39:15,645
I requested a restraining order

598
00:39:17,939 --> 00:39:20,900
so if you ever approach
Woo-joo or Hyun-jin again

599
00:39:23,444 --> 00:39:25,488
I won't let it slide.

600
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:30,034
Tae-hyung!

601
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:31,578
Tae-hyung!

602
00:39:31,661 --> 00:39:32,704
Tae-hyung!

603
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:52,056
THE LATE SUN WOO-JIN, WOO HYUN-JOO

604
00:39:56,603 --> 00:39:58,938
Hey, Woo-jin.

605
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:02,692
Sorry, I took so long.

606
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:09,240
I had no idea you protected me

607
00:40:12,452 --> 00:40:14,120
and loved me until the end.

608
00:40:19,042 --> 00:40:20,543
I'm sorry.

609
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:26,007
I'm so sorry, Woo-jin.

610
00:40:37,894 --> 00:40:43,566
SAETBYEOL DAYCARE

611
00:40:46,778 --> 00:40:47,779
Woo-joo!

612
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:51,032
Woo-joo! Your uncle is here today!

613
00:40:51,115 --> 00:40:52,283
Put your shoes on.

614
00:40:52,367 --> 00:40:53,743
Uncle!

615
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:55,828
Did you miss me?

616
00:40:55,912 --> 00:40:56,913
- My Woo-joo.
- Woo-joo

617
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:58,623
seems excited that you're here.

618
00:40:58,706 --> 00:40:59,874
Right, Woo-joo?

619
00:40:59,958 --> 00:41:01,376
Uncle Tae-hyung.

620
00:41:02,126 --> 00:41:03,962
That's right, Uncle Tae-hyung.

621
00:41:04,087 --> 00:41:05,672
Uncle Tae-hyung!

622
00:41:26,609 --> 00:41:27,735
Hey.

623
00:41:28,444 --> 00:41:30,154
I was waiting for you.

624
00:41:31,114 --> 00:41:33,324
Oh, really?

625
00:41:33,616 --> 00:41:34,909
You should've called.

626
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,411
Where's Woo-joo?

627
00:41:37,745 --> 00:41:39,497
He just fell asleep.

628
00:41:44,127 --> 00:41:46,587
What's all this?

629
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:48,006
Are you going somewhere?

630
00:41:54,012 --> 00:41:55,013
Yeah.

631
00:41:55,805 --> 00:41:57,473
It's about time I go home.

632
00:41:58,182 --> 00:41:59,183
Huh?

633
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:01,686
Go where?

634
00:42:02,854 --> 00:42:05,106
I've been lying to you all along.

635
00:42:07,025 --> 00:42:08,776
The house renovation ended weeks ago.

636
00:42:11,571 --> 00:42:14,532
Is this about what happened?

637
00:42:15,158 --> 00:42:16,534
With your father?

638
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:17,660
No.

639
00:42:18,786 --> 00:42:20,246
We agreed

640
00:42:20,663 --> 00:42:22,957
I'd only stay here for a month, anyway.

641
00:42:24,417 --> 00:42:25,960
It's time to leave now.

642
00:42:28,796 --> 00:42:29,797
Tae-hyung

643
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:35,720
I know you're doing this
because you feel bad about what happened.

644
00:42:35,803 --> 00:42:37,430
But we're family.

645
00:42:37,513 --> 00:42:39,432
We need to stick together all the more...

646
00:42:39,515 --> 00:42:41,059
You keep talking about being family

647
00:42:41,142 --> 00:42:42,935
but what does it even mean, anyway?

648
00:42:43,895 --> 00:42:45,438
I've never been family to anyone

649
00:42:45,521 --> 00:42:47,065
and I don't know how.

650
00:42:47,899 --> 00:42:49,984
- Tae-hyung...
- You saw it yourself.

651
00:42:50,068 --> 00:42:51,944
You saw what my father was like.

652
00:42:53,988 --> 00:42:55,740
I'm his son.

653
00:42:56,449 --> 00:42:58,910
That man is my family.

654
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:03,081
My whole life

655
00:43:03,164 --> 00:43:05,166
I've never been loved

656
00:43:05,249 --> 00:43:07,085
so all my life, I never noticed

657
00:43:07,168 --> 00:43:08,753
all the love I'd been getting.

658
00:43:10,546 --> 00:43:12,507
How can someone like me be family?

659
00:43:13,925 --> 00:43:16,886
I don't know how to do that
when I've never seen what it looks like.

660
00:43:17,136 --> 00:43:19,055
We can figure it out together.

661
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:21,724
We can figure it out together
like we've been doing...

662
00:43:21,808 --> 00:43:23,184
I thought

663
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:25,186
I could figure out how to be your family

664
00:43:26,270 --> 00:43:28,064
if I just gave it a try.

665
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:32,527
But I don't think so.

666
00:43:35,071 --> 00:43:37,281
I don't know how to protect anyone

667
00:43:39,033 --> 00:43:41,077
or love anyone properly.

668
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,829
So, how can I be anyone's family?

669
00:43:44,455 --> 00:43:45,873
And, to be honest

670
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:48,292
I don't think

671
00:43:49,210 --> 00:43:50,670
I can take care

672
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:53,798
of you or Woo-joo.

673
00:43:54,841 --> 00:43:56,092
My life is hard enough.

674
00:43:56,175 --> 00:43:58,052
I can't take care of anyone else.

675
00:44:01,097 --> 00:44:03,683
Who asked you to take care
of Woo-joo and me?

676
00:44:04,308 --> 00:44:06,644
And you think I'm confident
about raising a whole kid?

677
00:44:06,727 --> 00:44:09,272
No! I've never done it, either!

678
00:44:11,149 --> 00:44:12,859
But here I am, doing my best

679
00:44:12,942 --> 00:44:14,735
because I want you to stay with us.

680
00:44:15,987 --> 00:44:17,530
Don't you see my effort?

681
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:20,241
Don't make an effort for me, okay?

682
00:44:25,246 --> 00:44:28,207
Don't make an effort for me.
You'll only get hurt and disappointed.

683
00:44:30,835 --> 00:44:32,753
Let's just go our separate ways.

684
00:45:24,513 --> 00:45:25,640
<i>Woo-joo</i>

685
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:28,643
I don't think

686
00:45:29,810 --> 00:45:32,230
I can live with you anymore.

687
00:45:33,231 --> 00:45:36,275
I don't trust myself enough to do it.

688
00:45:36,651 --> 00:45:38,361
You don't trust yourself?

689
00:45:38,444 --> 00:45:39,779
I don't have the courage to.

690
00:45:42,281 --> 00:45:44,492
Just like your dad...

691
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:45,576
Yeah.

692
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:49,247
I'm worried your auntie will get hurt
because of me.

693
00:45:49,330 --> 00:45:50,623
I'm scared.

694
00:45:52,333 --> 00:45:54,919
But you know
I'm your uncle forever, right?

695
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:56,462
Yeah.

696
00:45:56,629 --> 00:45:58,005
Even if we don't live together

697
00:45:59,507 --> 00:46:02,051
I'll come and visit you often.

698
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:05,930
And we can go on fun trips together.

699
00:46:06,889 --> 00:46:08,099
- Okay?
- Yeah.

700
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:12,103
Okay

701
00:46:13,980 --> 00:46:15,147
so

702
00:46:16,065 --> 00:46:19,735
don't ever think I abandoned you, alright?

703
00:46:44,218 --> 00:46:45,845
Let's put on your socks.

704
00:46:45,928 --> 00:46:47,346
Perfect!

705
00:46:47,430 --> 00:46:49,140
Give me a sec.

706
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:51,434
Let me pack a handkerchief.

707
00:46:51,767 --> 00:46:55,146
Put it in the backpack.

708
00:46:55,229 --> 00:46:57,273
And your lunch.

709
00:46:57,356 --> 00:46:58,941
Water!

710
00:46:59,734 --> 00:47:01,610
- I MADE TOAST. DON'T FORGET TO EAT!
- THANK YOU!

711
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:05,031
- I MADE TOAST. DON'T FORGET TO EAT!
- THANK YOU!

712
00:47:05,114 --> 00:47:06,657
WOO-JOO HAD BREAKFAST AND LUNCH!
PLEASE PREPARE DINNER FOR HIM

713
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:08,367
- I'M WORKING LATE TONIGHT.
- OH, NO... GOOD LUCK!

714
00:47:14,206 --> 00:47:15,624
Let's go, Woo-joo!

715
00:47:15,708 --> 00:47:16,917
We're late.

716
00:47:18,044 --> 00:47:19,628
Skipped breakfast again?

717
00:47:19,837 --> 00:47:21,630
Have some before you take your meds.

718
00:47:21,714 --> 00:47:25,009
I know you don't like hot water,
but don't drink ice-cold water.

719
00:47:28,679 --> 00:47:30,097
I heard from my attorney

720
00:47:30,181 --> 00:47:32,058
that you agreed to sign the papers.

721
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:35,478
- Yeah.
- Why?

722
00:47:35,686 --> 00:47:38,189
Weren't you going to sue me
for more alimony?

723
00:47:39,065 --> 00:47:40,358
Sue you? Forget it.

724
00:47:42,401 --> 00:47:44,695
You're a celeb, you know?

725
00:47:44,779 --> 00:47:46,238
If the lawsuit drags on

726
00:47:46,322 --> 00:47:47,907
people will talk.

727
00:47:48,783 --> 00:47:49,992
You know it already.

728
00:47:50,076 --> 00:47:51,619
When are you quitting, then?

729
00:47:53,537 --> 00:47:55,247
- Hmm?
- We'll be divorced

730
00:47:55,331 --> 00:47:56,916
and you're done training Tae-hyung.

731
00:47:56,999 --> 00:47:58,417
You have no reason to be here.

732
00:47:59,877 --> 00:48:01,420
Yeah, I'll leave soon, alright.

733
00:48:02,004 --> 00:48:04,382
And you think
it just ends with training Tae-hyung?

734
00:48:04,465 --> 00:48:08,010
I've been waiting
for Tae-hyung to get settled properly.

735
00:48:08,302 --> 00:48:10,721
Stop bothering me. Just quit soon.

736
00:48:16,352 --> 00:48:17,353
Sorry, Mr. Park.

737
00:48:17,436 --> 00:48:19,814
I can't sit in the front
because I get carsick.

738
00:48:20,815 --> 00:48:21,899
It's okay.

739
00:48:21,982 --> 00:48:23,692
I prefer the front seats, anyway.

740
00:48:23,776 --> 00:48:25,361
By the way, Ms. Woo

741
00:48:25,444 --> 00:48:28,030
are you sure you're fine
with driving the whole way?

742
00:48:28,114 --> 00:48:29,740
Of course, don't worry.

743
00:48:29,824 --> 00:48:31,700
Get some sleep.

744
00:48:31,784 --> 00:48:33,619
It's going to be a long shoot today.

745
00:48:33,702 --> 00:48:34,954
No way!

746
00:48:35,329 --> 00:48:36,580
How can we take a nap

747
00:48:36,664 --> 00:48:38,541
when you're sitting right there?

748
00:48:38,624 --> 00:48:39,917
I know!

749
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:42,586
How can we sleep? We'd feel terrible.

750
00:48:50,886 --> 00:48:52,638
Let me know if you get tired.

751
00:48:53,013 --> 00:48:54,390
I can take over.

752
00:48:54,473 --> 00:48:55,933
Okay, will do.

753
00:48:56,684 --> 00:48:58,269
You should get some sleep, too.

754
00:48:58,352 --> 00:49:00,146
We still have a long way to go.

755
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:02,940
What's this, by the way?

756
00:49:03,774 --> 00:49:06,277
I just packed some snacks.

757
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:08,529
I assumed nobody had time to eat
in the morning.

758
00:49:09,155 --> 00:49:10,489
You can have some, too.

759
00:49:10,573 --> 00:49:12,116
I packed a lot.

760
00:49:18,038 --> 00:49:19,081
Open up.

761
00:49:20,666 --> 00:49:21,709
Yoon-seong!

762
00:49:22,793 --> 00:49:24,712
You don't look like you got much sleep.

763
00:49:24,795 --> 00:49:26,547
I just don't want you to get drowsy.

764
00:49:26,714 --> 00:49:28,174
Come on. Open.

765
00:49:31,010 --> 00:49:32,011
Thank you.

766
00:49:52,490 --> 00:49:53,908
You can stand here.

767
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:56,869
Please review the storyboard for today.

768
00:49:59,371 --> 00:50:02,583
- Just casually scoop some <i>gochujang.</i>
- Okay.

769
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:04,668
Try to look as natural as possible.

770
00:50:04,752 --> 00:50:05,753
Okay.

771
00:50:06,420 --> 00:50:08,130
Try to keep all your hair back...

772
00:50:08,631 --> 00:50:10,382
Here's the storyboard, Mr. Park.

773
00:50:13,219 --> 00:50:14,553
Did you check it?

774
00:50:15,179 --> 00:50:16,555
- Yeah.
- Look at that.

775
00:50:16,972 --> 00:50:18,682
This hairspray is awesome!

776
00:50:18,766 --> 00:50:20,601
Have some coffee, everyone!

777
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:22,645
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

778
00:50:29,318 --> 00:50:31,362
That's good.

779
00:50:48,879 --> 00:50:50,631
I'm serious!

780
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:53,133
Don't you see what's going on
between them?

781
00:50:53,592 --> 00:50:55,469
They're 100% dating.

782
00:50:56,053 --> 00:50:58,514
I definitely saw it in the car.

783
00:50:58,597 --> 00:51:00,766
He fed her candy!

784
00:51:01,517 --> 00:51:03,852
Really? Gosh, I'm jealous!

785
00:51:03,936 --> 00:51:05,354
Ms. Woo got lucky!

786
00:51:05,437 --> 00:51:07,398
You can't find a better man than Mr. Park.

787
00:51:07,481 --> 00:51:09,275
He's smart, successful, rich

788
00:51:09,358 --> 00:51:11,193
and from a good family! He's perfect.

789
00:51:11,735 --> 00:51:13,112
- Right?
- Lucky her.

790
00:51:13,195 --> 00:51:14,280
- Seung-taek.
- Yes?

791
00:51:14,363 --> 00:51:16,198
The sunlight is good.
Let's keep it natural.

792
00:51:16,282 --> 00:51:17,992
- Without the reflector.
- Got it.

793
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:20,744
We'll change the lighting
and get started right away!

794
00:51:20,828 --> 00:51:22,663
Gosh, Tae-hyung.

795
00:51:22,746 --> 00:51:24,498
He's so calm for his first shoot.

796
00:51:24,582 --> 00:51:26,041
The guy's born talented.

797
00:51:40,973 --> 00:51:45,060
Have you checked the spot in the proposal?

798
00:51:45,144 --> 00:51:46,186
Yeah.

799
00:51:46,687 --> 00:51:48,606
It's along the center of that staircase.

800
00:51:49,148 --> 00:51:50,566
At the top, right?

801
00:52:03,621 --> 00:52:07,541
We won't even need much editing on this.

802
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:09,585
What do you think?

803
00:52:09,918 --> 00:52:10,961
Looks great.

804
00:52:11,045 --> 00:52:13,088
- Good, right?
- Yeah, it's great.

805
00:52:26,226 --> 00:52:27,603
How's this setup?

806
00:52:27,686 --> 00:52:29,396
Why don't we go with it if you're fine?

807
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:30,731
- It looks good.
- Okay.

808
00:52:31,690 --> 00:52:32,941
That'd look more appetizing.

809
00:52:33,359 --> 00:52:34,360
Looks great.

810
00:52:34,443 --> 00:52:36,070
How does this look, Mr. Sun?

811
00:52:47,873 --> 00:52:49,124
Looks great. Let's keep it.

812
00:52:49,208 --> 00:52:50,417
We'll begin the shoot!

813
00:52:50,501 --> 00:52:51,835
Okay.

814
00:52:52,670 --> 00:52:53,712
Oh, no!

815
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:00,928
- Mr. Park!
- Hyun-jin.

816
00:53:01,011 --> 00:53:02,012
- Are you okay?
- Mr. Park!

817
00:53:02,096 --> 00:53:03,138
- Are you okay, Hyun-jin?
- Are you okay?

818
00:53:03,222 --> 00:53:04,264
Are you okay?

819
00:53:05,391 --> 00:53:06,392
Oh, no.

820
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:09,019
Are you okay?

821
00:53:10,104 --> 00:53:11,146
Let's get up.

822
00:53:15,693 --> 00:53:17,403
Shouldn't you see a doctor?

823
00:53:17,820 --> 00:53:19,071
- I'm fine.
- No!

824
00:53:19,154 --> 00:53:21,490
Get some ointment on, at least!

825
00:53:21,573 --> 00:53:22,866
You, too, Hyun-jin!

826
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:25,035
Come! Let's get you some ointment!

827
00:53:29,248 --> 00:53:30,541
Hurry!

828
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:33,293
Where's the emergency kit?

829
00:53:33,836 --> 00:53:35,713
Please hand me the emergency kit!

830
00:53:36,004 --> 00:53:37,131
Hurry!

831
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:45,055
What were you thinking?
You shouldn't have jumped in.

832
00:53:45,764 --> 00:53:48,434
Are you really fine?

833
00:53:50,602 --> 00:53:52,855
Huh? Why are you laughing?

834
00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:57,025
It's just a little burn, that's all.

835
00:53:57,484 --> 00:53:59,027
You must've been scared.

836
00:54:00,988 --> 00:54:01,989
Same.

837
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:04,450
So scary!

838
00:54:04,825 --> 00:54:06,785
I'm really fine, okay?

839
00:54:08,704 --> 00:54:11,248
Thanks. I mean it.

840
00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:16,962
The photos look amazing.

841
00:54:17,045 --> 00:54:18,172
Right?

842
00:54:18,255 --> 00:54:20,758
Is Mr. Park okay?

843
00:54:21,049 --> 00:54:23,302
Thankfully, it wasn't a big injury.

844
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:25,012
Gosh, that scared me.

845
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:27,598
It could've been really bad.

846
00:54:27,681 --> 00:54:28,932
How did he jump in like that?

847
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:30,934
Maybe it's because he's so young.

848
00:54:31,018 --> 00:54:32,603
No, it's not his age.

849
00:54:33,145 --> 00:54:34,813
It's about his heart.

850
00:54:35,147 --> 00:54:36,148
His heart?

851
00:54:36,231 --> 00:54:39,109
He jumped in to save her in a flash

852
00:54:39,693 --> 00:54:42,696
because he moved without a second thought.

853
00:54:42,780 --> 00:54:43,947
To guard Ms. Woo.

854
00:54:44,031 --> 00:54:45,866
Guard her? Why?

855
00:54:52,164 --> 00:54:55,042
Hey! You know nothing.

856
00:54:55,125 --> 00:54:57,252
What are you talking about?

857
00:54:57,336 --> 00:54:59,004
I probably know it better than you all.

858
00:54:59,087 --> 00:55:01,465
Better than us all? Just look.

859
00:55:01,590 --> 00:55:04,760
Ms. Woo looks so much better
with Tae-hyung.

860
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,512
What are you talking about?

861
00:55:06,595 --> 00:55:09,723
Ms. Woo looks cuter with Mr. Park!

862
00:55:09,807 --> 00:55:12,017
Hey! That's just wrong.

863
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:14,311
Ms. Woo and Tae-hyung look
like the perfect match!

864
00:55:14,394 --> 00:55:16,563
Huh? No, you're wrong.

865
00:55:16,647 --> 00:55:18,941
She has way more chemistry with Mr. Park!

866
00:55:19,024 --> 00:55:22,069
You're really clueless, aren't you?

867
00:55:23,111 --> 00:55:24,154
Oh!

868
00:55:24,613 --> 00:55:26,782
You've never had a girlfriend, have you?

869
00:55:26,865 --> 00:55:28,659
- Huh?
- Definitely.

870
00:55:30,285 --> 00:55:31,954
- Forever alone.
- "Forever alone"?

871
00:55:33,121 --> 00:55:34,915
What's wrong with being single?

872
00:55:34,998 --> 00:55:36,834
Nothing. But you've never dated anyone.

873
00:55:37,876 --> 00:55:39,711
I chose this single life!

874
00:55:40,170 --> 00:55:41,380
I'm married.

875
00:55:42,631 --> 00:55:44,174
I know love when I see it.

876
00:55:45,217 --> 00:55:46,760
Women love me!

877
00:55:55,519 --> 00:55:58,647
<i>He jumped in to save her in a flash</i>

878
00:55:58,730 --> 00:56:01,441
<i>because his body reacted</i>
<i>before he could think.</i>

879
00:56:01,525 --> 00:56:02,568
<i>To guard Ms. Woo.</i>

880
00:56:02,651 --> 00:56:04,528
<i>You can't find a better man than Mr. Park.</i>

881
00:56:04,611 --> 00:56:06,238
<i>He's smart, successful, rich</i>

882
00:56:06,321 --> 00:56:08,073
<i>and from a good family! He's perfect.</i>

883
00:56:16,999 --> 00:56:19,668
All of it seems almost new.
You sure I can have them all?

884
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:20,752
Yeah.

885
00:56:21,837 --> 00:56:24,756
I've been looking to get rid of them

886
00:56:25,257 --> 00:56:27,050
because they were taking up space, anyway.

887
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:29,219
I mean, I'm happy to take them.

888
00:56:29,887 --> 00:56:31,555
Are you going to continue living here?

889
00:56:32,306 --> 00:56:33,432
What about you?

890
00:56:33,724 --> 00:56:35,642
Have you really moved
out of Hyun-jin's house?

891
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:38,604
You didn't have to go that far.

892
00:56:41,899 --> 00:56:43,025
I know

893
00:56:43,984 --> 00:56:45,903
but I'm too ashamed to see Hyun-jin now.

894
00:56:46,320 --> 00:56:47,362
Why?

895
00:56:47,821 --> 00:56:49,323
Because your father hurt her?

896
00:56:50,365 --> 00:56:51,533
You know

897
00:56:52,576 --> 00:56:54,119
Hyun-jin's been through a lot

898
00:56:54,786 --> 00:56:56,288
since her sister passed away.

899
00:56:57,998 --> 00:57:00,959
She couldn't even bring herself

900
00:57:01,418 --> 00:57:02,961
to go to her sister's room alone.

901
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:09,676
And if you think about it,
I caused her death.

902
00:57:11,053 --> 00:57:12,304
What about Hyun-jin?

903
00:57:12,804 --> 00:57:14,932
Does she know about you and your brother?

904
00:57:16,975 --> 00:57:20,103
I'll keep it a secret.
She'll get worried if she finds out.

905
00:57:21,104 --> 00:57:22,773
Are you sure you'll be fine?

906
00:57:24,483 --> 00:57:26,109
I know you like her.

907
00:57:30,113 --> 00:57:33,742
How do you know that?

908
00:57:34,409 --> 00:57:36,954
I've known you forever.

909
00:57:37,037 --> 00:57:38,330
You didn't think I'd notice?

910
00:57:41,083 --> 00:57:42,292
Yeah, I like her.

911
00:57:44,336 --> 00:57:45,629
Wouldn't it be better

912
00:57:46,588 --> 00:57:49,091
to stay by her side?

913
00:57:54,805 --> 00:57:55,889
I don't know.

914
00:57:56,682 --> 00:57:59,059
Would having me by her side be any help?

915
00:58:02,562 --> 00:58:05,565
Especially when there's a man by her side

916
00:58:06,483 --> 00:58:08,402
who's clearly much better than I am?

917
00:58:11,071 --> 00:58:12,155
You know

918
00:58:13,448 --> 00:58:17,619
I think it'll just be best for me
to wish she meets someone great

919
00:58:18,286 --> 00:58:19,538
like Mr. Park.

920
00:58:24,126 --> 00:58:25,919
- Your auntie is here.
- Hello.

921
00:58:26,169 --> 00:58:27,462
Woo-joo!

922
00:58:28,588 --> 00:58:30,507
Sorry, I'm so late.

923
00:58:30,590 --> 00:58:32,134
The meeting ran really long.

924
00:58:32,217 --> 00:58:35,137
It's fine. Work can get busy.

925
00:58:35,387 --> 00:58:37,097
By the way

926
00:58:37,180 --> 00:58:40,851
is it true that Woo-joo's uncle moved out?

927
00:58:43,145 --> 00:58:45,355
Yeah, he moved out.

928
00:58:45,689 --> 00:58:47,649
Did you two fight?

929
00:58:50,235 --> 00:58:51,319
No.

930
00:58:51,778 --> 00:58:54,573
Good. Don't fight, okay?

931
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:57,909
I felt so proud,
watching you two figure life out

932
00:58:57,993 --> 00:59:01,163
and raising Woo-joo together.

933
00:59:02,539 --> 00:59:03,915
Oh, right.

934
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:08,295
There's a show happening

935
00:59:08,378 --> 00:59:10,005
at Woo-joo's daycare.

936
00:59:10,505 --> 00:59:13,383
Call Tae-hyung and go together.

937
00:59:14,801 --> 00:59:16,887
- Roar!
- Roar!

938
00:59:16,970 --> 00:59:18,346
Is that what you learned today?

939
00:59:18,555 --> 00:59:19,681
It was so much fun.

940
00:59:19,973 --> 00:59:22,559
I'm glad you had all your food today.

941
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:24,728
What's this?

942
00:59:29,524 --> 00:59:32,903
<i>There's a show happening</i>

943
00:59:33,487 --> 00:59:36,490
<i>at Woo-joo's daycare.</i>

944
00:59:36,573 --> 00:59:37,824
<i>I hear Bom is inviting</i>

945
00:59:37,908 --> 00:59:40,869
<i>even her grandparents.</i>

946
00:59:47,292 --> 00:59:49,628
TEMPORARY HELPER

947
00:59:52,214 --> 00:59:53,340
TEMPORARY HELPER

948
00:59:55,801 --> 00:59:56,802
Forget it.

949
00:59:58,011 --> 00:59:59,096
It's just a little show.

950
00:59:59,179 --> 01:00:00,305
Peek-a-boo!

951
01:00:00,597 --> 01:00:02,432
Did you practice for the show today?

952
01:00:02,516 --> 01:00:05,102
- Yeah.
- Really?

953
01:00:05,352 --> 01:00:06,812
Say hi to your teacher!

954
01:00:06,895 --> 01:00:08,105
Hello!

955
01:00:08,188 --> 01:00:09,481
You ready to do great today?

956
01:00:09,564 --> 01:00:10,565
Come here.

957
01:00:10,649 --> 01:00:12,025
Let's take a photo. Come here.

958
01:00:12,109 --> 01:00:13,819
Could you take a photo for us?

959
01:00:13,902 --> 01:00:15,237
Here we go! One, two...

960
01:00:15,946 --> 01:00:18,115
Cheese! Right on!

961
01:00:18,323 --> 01:00:19,616
- Hello!
- Hello!

962
01:00:19,699 --> 01:00:21,535
- Hello!
- Say hi to your teacher!

963
01:00:21,618 --> 01:00:23,036
- Hi!
- Hello!

964
01:00:23,870 --> 01:00:25,831
Come this way.

965
01:00:25,914 --> 01:00:28,625
Another one! Cheese!

966
01:00:29,918 --> 01:00:31,419
Look at you! You look adorable.

967
01:00:31,503 --> 01:00:33,880
- See you!
- Let's head in.

968
01:00:34,381 --> 01:00:35,507
You can do it!

969
01:00:41,930 --> 01:00:44,224
Maybe I should've gotten
a bigger bouquet, at least.

970
01:00:47,269 --> 01:00:48,270
Hyun-jin!

971
01:00:49,521 --> 01:00:50,605
Oh, hey.

972
01:00:50,689 --> 01:00:52,274
Why are you just standing around?

973
01:00:52,649 --> 01:00:54,651
Well, I didn't realize

974
01:00:54,734 --> 01:00:56,486
this show was such a big event.

975
01:00:56,570 --> 01:00:58,613
Oh, I guess you're new to this.

976
01:00:58,697 --> 01:01:00,657
I should've told you in advance.

977
01:01:02,409 --> 01:01:04,828
Where's Tae-hyung?
He didn't come with you?

978
01:01:05,078 --> 01:01:07,122
You should've invited him.

979
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:10,667
Yeah, I should've.

980
01:01:11,209 --> 01:01:12,919
Mom, take a photo of me.

981
01:01:13,378 --> 01:01:14,379
Okay.

982
01:01:14,462 --> 01:01:16,006
- See you later.
- Yeah.

983
01:01:16,089 --> 01:01:17,090
Let's go!

984
01:01:17,340 --> 01:01:18,341
Let's take one there.

985
01:01:21,428 --> 01:01:23,555
Who's the prettiest girl?

986
01:01:24,681 --> 01:01:27,017
One, two, three! Make a heart!

987
01:01:27,559 --> 01:01:30,770
Make a giant heart! Good girl!

988
01:01:31,897 --> 01:01:33,732
TODAY'S SUPERSTAR, KIM HA-MIN

989
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:35,483
Hello!

990
01:01:35,567 --> 01:01:37,319
- Hello.
- Hi.

991
01:01:41,323 --> 01:01:43,450
JEONGWOON ELEMENTARY SCHOOL FIELD DAY

992
01:01:55,295 --> 01:01:58,423
Make a giant heart! Good girl!

993
01:02:00,675 --> 01:02:02,969
One, two, three!

994
01:02:03,261 --> 01:02:04,638
Perfect!

995
01:02:07,807 --> 01:02:10,518
Parents, please head inside.

996
01:02:10,602 --> 01:02:12,604
Kids, come and get ready.

997
01:02:15,357 --> 01:02:16,983
Let's go in, Woo-joo.

998
01:02:19,486 --> 01:02:23,198
SAETBYEOL DAYCARE ANNUAL SHOW

999
01:02:26,618 --> 01:02:27,911
Woo-joo!

1000
01:02:29,079 --> 01:02:30,080
Woo-joo!

1001
01:02:30,372 --> 01:02:31,998
Huh? Woo-joo!

1002
01:02:32,082 --> 01:02:33,124
Where are you going?

1003
01:02:33,208 --> 01:02:34,876
I'll see what's going on. I'll be back.

1004
01:02:36,169 --> 01:02:37,212
Woo-joo!

1005
01:03:43,445 --> 01:03:45,697
OUR UNIVERSE

1006
01:03:45,780 --> 01:03:47,073
Woo-joo!

1007
01:03:48,325 --> 01:03:50,452
<i>You were amazing today!</i>

1008
01:03:50,535 --> 01:03:53,079
<i>No need to feel like you owe me anything</i>
<i>between us.</i>

1009
01:03:53,330 --> 01:03:55,332
<i>So, have you decided?</i>

1010
01:03:55,623 --> 01:03:57,667
<i>Oh, we don't live together anymore.</i>

1011
01:03:57,959 --> 01:03:59,919
<i>Woo-joo, want to go on a date with me?</i>

1012
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:02,505
<i>I'll get going now, Woo-joo.</i>

1013
01:04:03,798 --> 01:04:05,091
<i>My heart feels heavy.</i>

1014
01:04:05,175 --> 01:04:07,260
<i>Anyway, it's so frustrating</i>
<i>to watch those two.</i>

1015
01:04:07,344 --> 01:04:09,929
<i>Moo-saeng is definitely not over Amy.</i>
<i>Why is he leaving?</i>

1016
01:04:10,013 --> 01:04:11,222
<i>This evening.</i>

1017
01:04:11,306 --> 01:04:13,516
<i>Yeah, I might as well buy it</i>
<i>while I'm there.</i>

1018
01:04:25,195 --> 01:04:27,197
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
